reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was hesitant to order this sweater because of mixed reviews that I read. Glad I purchased this sweater. It is light weight, soft and comfortable. The pattern and color are great as well. Sleeve length is always an issue for me but these sleeves are plenty long. After reading the reviews, I did size down and the fit is perfect.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A nice, blocky sweater for fall and layering - GRACE KARIN is great
reviews.reviewText: The GRACE KARIN Women's Turtleneck Sweater is a fashion-forward and cozy addition to your fall wardrobe. With lantern sleeves and an oversized chunky cable knit design, it perfectly blends elegance and comfort. Here's what makes it a standout choice:Trendy Turtleneck: The turtleneck design offers warmth and style, making it suitable for various fall outings and activities.Lantern Sleeve Elegance: The lantern sleeves add a touch of sophistication and uniqueness to this sweater, making it perfect for both casual and more dressed-up occasions.Chunky Cable Knit: Crafted with chunky cable knit fabric, this sweater offers both style and comfort, ensuring you stay cozy and chic throughout the fall season.Oversized Versatility: The oversized fit not only adds to the comfort but also provides versatility, allowing you to pair it with different bottoms and accessories.The sweater is a little itchy but think any sweater with this material would be, so wear a long sleeve shirt underneath vs. a camisole and you should be fine!

reviews.reviewText: Love how this sweater looks and feels. However, after a few wears it’s pilling a lot.I usually wear a medium or large top, depending on the brand and the medium sweater fits well. A small would probably also fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty sweater if you are into bulky but made very well
reviews.reviewText: Cute sweater, just fits tight over head and its pretty bulky, which I am getting away from. The small is huge. I am 5'3 and 120. You can tuck in the front and its fine so I will keep it. Color and quality are great over all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Tiny Bit Scratchy but Very Pretty, Flattering Fit
reviews.reviewText: The first thing I noticed about this sweater was how beautiful the color is and how attractive the diamond shape design on the front is. This adds some cute elegance to it! I also really like the fit. It’s a little looser but still flattering for that chic cozy look. It looks thicker than it is, it has nice girth to the material but is light and airy, which i love. It’s easy to layer over a T-shirt or tank but can comfortably fit under a jacket or blazer. It as has some nice flexibility and stretch to it as well.I found it very comfortable but it could be a just little scratchy for those who can be sensitive. I am one who can be pretty affected by rougher textures but i still found this comfortable. The neck was where I most noticed it being a tad scratchy. But overall it’s very cozy! Again, the material is flexible and light so it will keep you warm but it’s not too thick or bulky.Overall i am very happy and I look forward to wearing it more now that autumn has arrived! I definitely give this cute sweater my recommendation :)
